==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)k|-ɑː(r)k]]

===Verb===
'''to hark'''

# To listen attentively.

# (hark back to) Remember something in the past or remind someone of it.
#: Harking back to the theme of a series of speeches he delivered last week, he said he was reminded that “there’s still an enemy out there that would like to inflict the same kind of damage again.”'' &mdash; [http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/11/nyregion/nyregionspecial3/11bush.html?hp&ex=1158033600&en=e468f88da52557ed&ei=5094&partner=homepage New York Times]
===Interjection===
'''hark'''
# ''(archaic)'' Listen (to me)
#:'' '''Hark!''' I have a tale to tell! ''

